      "comment_id" : 89975954,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "@Demigod <code>LocalDateTime.ofEpochSecond(…)</code> requires an actual <code>ZoneOffset</code>, but  <code>ZoneId.systemDefault()</code> returns a <code>ZoneId</code>. A <code>ZoneId</code> can map to different offsets, depending on the point of time you’re referring to. That’s what <code>LocalDateTime.ofInstant</code> does for you, converting the specified <code>ZoneId</code> according to the provided <code>Instant</code>."
    }, {
